# Internationalization (i18n) Rules

## Mandatory Locales

English (`en`) and Polish (`pl`) are **mandatory**. Both must be 100% complete at all times. CI fails on any missing PL key.

## No Hardcoded Strings — Zero Exceptions

Every user-facing string **must** go through `t('namespace:key')`. This is not optional.

**Before writing any JSX or returning any string to the user, ask:** *"Would a user see this?"* If yes, it must be translated.

Strings that must always be translated:
- Button labels, link text, tab labels (including dynamic defaults like "New Tab")
- Input `placeholder`, `aria-label`, `title`, `alt` attributes
- Empty state titles and descriptions
- Error messages, success messages, loading indicators
- Navigation labels, page/section headers, breadcrumbs
- Confirmation dialog text, tooltip content
- Fallback strings (e.g. `note.title || t('notes:untitled')` — not `|| 'Untitled'`)

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<Button>{t('common:save')}</Button>
<Input placeholder={t('notes:searchPlaceholder')} />
<EmptyState title={t('notes:emptyTitle')} description={t('notes:emptyDescription')} />
const tab = makeTab(note, t('common:newTab'))   // dynamic default
note.title || t('notes:untitled')               // fallback string

// ❌ BAD — every one of these is a bug
<Button>Save</Button>
<Input placeholder="Search notes..." />
<EmptyState title="No notes yet" description="Create your first note" />
const tab = makeTab(note, 'New Tab')
note.title || 'Untitled'
```

## Enforcement Checklist (run before every commit)

When you write or edit a `.tsx` / `.ts` file, scan for these patterns and replace every hit:

| Pattern | Replace with |
|---------|-------------|
| `"..."` or `'...'` as JSX children | `{t('ns:key')}` |
| `placeholder="..."` | `placeholder={t('ns:key')}` |
| `aria-label="..."` | `aria-label={t('ns:key')}` (unless purely decorative) |
| `title="..."` on interactive elements | `title={t('ns:key')}` |
| `\|\| 'fallback'` for display text | `\|\| t('ns:key')` |

## Adding New Strings

1. Add the key to the appropriate `packages/i18n/src/locales/en/{namespace}.json` first.
2. **Immediately** add the Polish translation to `pl/{namespace}.json` in the same response.
3. Use ICU MessageFormat for plurals and interpolation.
4. Rebuild `@locus/i18n` (`pnpm --filter @locus/i18n build`) so TypeScript types update.

```json
// en/tasks.json
{ "activeCount": "{count, plural, one {# task} other {# tasks}}" }

// pl/tasks.json
{ "activeCount": "{count, plural, one {# zadanie} few {# zadania} many {# zadań} other {# zadań}}" }
```

## Date & Number Formatting

Use `Intl.DateTimeFormat` and `Intl.NumberFormat` with the active locale. Never hardcode date formats like `MM/DD/YYYY` or timestamp strings.

## AI Output

When the user's locale is not English, AI prompts must include `Respond in {locale name}` to match the user's language.
